column5: Has anyone ever been here? Just curious what people that stayed there thought? <{{}}><

I was there for a short trip 7-8 years ago. Clean place. We did our own cooking. The fishing was good. We had to work for them but managed. Got a belly full of Blue in the lodge one night and the people were very nice.
Sure looks like a nice place! It would be nice if somebody could help you out!

We also caught some very nice smallies. The walleye were deep but would come up later in the day. We fished around the islands not far from camp and this was in early September. Don't know what the prices are today but then I thought they were very reasonable.
Apparently the owner is co-heading a new group to combat illegal and irresponsible netting on LOTW, so at least you know the owner is a good guy and worth supporting.
